subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Body length range (n=7): 0.57 to 0.70 mm. 
Holotype
: 0.70 mm. Color blue gray in ethanol (
Fig.1
). Secondary granules moderately developed. Antennae shorter than cephalic diagonal; ratio antennae: cephalic diagonal = 1: 1.3. Ant IV with simple apical bulb, subapical organite and dorsolateral microsensillum present, 4 thick sensilla, 3 dorso-external and 1 dorso-internal (
Fig.2a
). Ventral chaetotaxy of Ant IV composed of short and long chaetae. Ventral separation of Ant III and IV marked (
Fig.2b
). Sensory organ of Ant III with two small internal microsensilla, two long guard chaetae, and one microsensillum (
Figs 2a
). Ant II with 12–13 chaetae. Ant I with 7 chaetae.

Tibiotarsi I–III with 19,19,18 chaetae, respectively; 2 dorsal clavate tenent hairs each. Ungues simple, without inner tooth. Empodial appendix absent (
Figs 3a, 3b
).

Sternites of Th II–III usually without chaetae. Ventral tube with 4+4 chaetae (
Fig. 3c
). Ventral quetotaxy of abdominal segments as follows: Abd II–V with 7–8+7–8, 6+6, 4+4, 5–6+5–6 chaetae, respectively (
Fig. 3d
). Tenaculum with 3+3 teeth. Furca developed; manubrium with up to 28 chaetae; each dens with 2 chaetae; mucro simple, separated from the dens and with a thin lamella and curved apex (
Fig. 3e
). Abd VI with two anal spines on papilla. Anal valves with 14+14 chaetae, hr chaetae not visualized. Female genital plate with 3 + 3 pregenital setae, 10 circumgenital setae and 1 + 1 eugenital (
Fig. 3f
); male genital plate with 3 + 3 pregenital setae, 14 circumgenital and 4 + 4 eugenital.
